  "text": "## SSO Settings API Feature Flag Control Chain: End-to-End Tracing\n\nThe `ssoSettingsApi` feature flag implements a comprehensive control mechanism spanning four architectural layers in Grafana v11.4.0:\n\n### 1. Feature Flag Definition & Generated Constants\n\nThe control begins with the feature flag definition in `pkg/services/featuremgmt/registry.go`, where `ssoSettingsApi` is registered with the description \"Enables the SSO settings API and the OAuth configuration UIs in Grafana\". This definition is code-generated into two constants files:\n- **Go**: `pkg/services/featuremgmt/toggles_gen.go` exports `FlagSsoSettingsApi = \"ssoSettingsApi\"`\n- **TypeScript**: `packages/grafana-data/src/types/featureToggles.gen.ts` generates `ssoSettingsApi?: boolean` property\n\nThese generated files ensure type-safe feature flag references across both backend and frontend layers.\n\n### 2. SSO Settings Infrastructure Layer\n\nThe infrastructure is built on a clean interface-based architecture defined in `pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettings.go`:\n\n**Service Interface** provides CRUD operations and configuration management:\n- `List()` / `ListWithRedactedSecrets()` - retrieve all SSO settings from DB and config files\n- `GetForProvider()` / `GetForProviderWithRedactedSecrets()` - provider-specific retrieval\n- `Upsert()` / `Delete()` / `Patch()` - persistent configuration modifications\n- `RegisterReloadable()` / `Reload()` - live configuration reloading support\n\n**Reloadable Interface** allows providers to validate and reload settings:\n- `Reload(ctx, settings)` - apply new settings to a provider\n- `Validate(ctx, settings, oldSettings, requester)` - pre-apply validation and authorization checks\n\n**Data Model** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/models/models.go`) defines `SSOSettings` struct with persistence annotations:\n- `xorm:\"id pk\"`, `xorm:\"provider\"`, `xorm:\"settings\"` - ORM table mapping to `sso_setting` table\n- `MarshalJSON`/`UnmarshalJSON` - automatic camelCase/snake_case conversion for API compatibility\n- `SettingsSource` enum (DB vs System) tracks configuration source\n\n**Store Interface** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettings.go`) abstracts database persistence:\n- Implemented by `SSOSettingsStore` in `pkg/services/ssosettings/database/database.go`\n- Provides Get, List, Upsert, Delete operations\n- `ProvideStore(sqlStore db.DB)` factory creates the store instance\n\n### 3. API & Authentication Wiring Layer\n\n**API Endpoint Registration** in `pkg/services/ssosettings/api/api.go`:\n\nThe `Api` struct receives `ssosettings.Service` dependency and registers REST endpoints at the `/api/v1/sso-settings` route group:\n```go\nfunc (api *Api) RegisterAPIEndpoints() {\n  api.RouteRegister.Group(\"/api/v1/sso-settings\", func(router routing.RouteRegister) {\n    auth := ac.Middleware(api.AccessControl)\n    router.Get(\"/\", auth(ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead)), ...)\n    router.Get(\"/:key\", auth(ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead, settingsScope)), ...)\n    router.Put(\"/:key\", auth(ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsWrite, settingsScope)), ...)\n    router.Delete(\"/:key\", auth(ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsWrite, settingsScope)), ...)\n  })\n}\n```\n\nEach endpoint is wrapped with access control middleware enforcing:\n- `ActionSettingsRead` permission for GET operations\n- `ActionSettingsWrite` permission for PUT/DELETE operations\n- Scoped to `ScopeSettingsOAuth(\":provider\")` for provider-specific access control\n\n**Service Integration via DI** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettingsimpl/service.go`):\n\nThe `ProvideService` function is the critical integration point that:\n1. Creates fallback strategies for OAuth, LDAP, and SAML configurations\n2. **Conditionally enables providers based on feature flags**:\n   - LDAP added to provider list if `FlagSsoSettingsLDAP` is enabled\n   - SAML added if enterprise license enables it AND `FlagSsoSettingsSAML` flag is enabled\n3. **Registers API only when flag is enabled**:\n   ```go\n   if features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) {\n     ssoSettingsApi := api.ProvideApi(svc, routeRegister, ac)\n     ssoSettingsApi.RegisterAPIEndpoints()\n   }\n   ```\n\nThis ensures the REST API infrastructure is only initialized when the feature flag is active.\n\n**OAuth Connector Loading** (`pkg/login/social/socialimpl/service.go`):\n\nThe `SocialService` receives `ssosettings.Service` as a dependency. In its initialization:\n```go\nif s.features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) {\n  allSettings, err := ssoSettings.List(context.Background())\n  // Load OAuth connectors from SSO settings\n}\n```\n\nWhen enabled, OAuth connectors are loaded from the SSO settings service, enabling dynamic OAuth provider configuration without restart.\n\n**LDAP Authentication Registration** (`pkg/services/ldap/service/ldap.go`):\n\nThe LDAP service's `ProvideService` function demonstrates the Reloadable integration:\n```go\nif s.features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) && \n   s.features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsLDAP) {\n  s.ssoSettings.RegisterReloadable(social.LDAPProviderName, s)\n}\n```\n\nLDAP registers itself as a Reloadable provider, enabling live LDAP configuration reloading when SSO settings are updated in the database without requiring service restart.\n\n### 4. Access Control & Dependency Injection Layer\n\n**Access Control Evaluators** (`pkg/services/accesscontrol/ssoutils/utils.go`):\n\nTwo evaluators gate access to the SSO settings UI and API:\n\n1. **EvalAuthenticationSettings** - for SAML and LDAP:\n   ```go\n   func EvalAuthenticationSettings(cfg *setting.Cfg) ac.Evaluator {\n     return ac.EvalAny(\n       ac.EvalAll(ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsWrite, ac.ScopeSettingsSAML),\n                  ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead, ac.ScopeSettingsSAML)),\n       ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionLDAPStatusRead))\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **OauthSettingsEvaluator** - for OAuth providers:\n   ```go\n   func OauthSettingsEvaluator(cfg *setting.Cfg) ac.Evaluator {\n     result := make([]ac.Evaluator, 0, len(cfg.SSOSettingsConfigurableProviders))\n     for provider := range cfg.SSOSettingsConfigurableProviders {\n       result = append(result, ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead, ac.ScopeSettingsOAuth(provider)))\n       result = append(result, ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsWrite, ac.ScopeSettingsOAuth(provider)))\n     }\n     return ac.EvalAny(result...)\n   }\n   ```\n\nThese evaluators build permission checks from the configured providers in `cfg.SSOSettingsConfigurableProviders`.\n\n**API Route Protection** (`pkg/api/api.go`):\n\nThe admin authentication UI routes demonstrate flag-gated access control:\n```go\nadminAuthPageEvaluator := func() ac.Evaluator {\n  authnSettingsEval := ssoutils.EvalAuthenticationSettings(hs.Cfg)\n  if hs.Features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) {\n    return ac.EvalAny(authnSettingsEval, ssoutils.OauthSettingsEvaluator(hs.Cfg))\n  }\n  return authnSettingsEval\n}\n\nr.Get(\"/admin/authentication\", authorize(adminAuthPageEvaluator()), hs.Index)\nif hs.Features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) {\n  r.Get(\"/admin/authentication/:provider\", authorize(ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead, ac.ScopeSettingsOAuth(providerParam))), hs.Index)\n}\n```\n\nWhen the flag is enabled, the evaluator includes `OauthSettingsEvaluator`, granting access to provider-specific authentication configuration UI.\n\n**Dependency Injection Registration** (`pkg/server/wire.go`):\n\nThe Wire dependency injection framework orchestrates all components:\n```go\nssoSettingsImpl.ProvideService,\nwire.Bind(new(ssosettings.Service), new(*ssoSettingsImpl.Service)),\n```\n\nThis ensures:\n- `ProvideService` is called during application initialization\n- The Service interface is bound to the concrete implementation\n- All service dependencies (db, routing, access control, features) are transitively satisfied\n- The complete service graph respects the feature flag gates\n\n## Control Flow Summary\n\n**When `ssoSettingsApi` feature flag is DISABLED:**\n- `pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettingsimpl/service.go` (line 94-97) skips API registration\n- `pkg/api/api.go` routes for `/admin/authentication/:provider` are not registered\n- `OauthSettingsEvaluator` is not included in access control checks\n- Frontend omits SSO settings UI components\n\n**When `ssoSettingsApi` feature flag is ENABLED:**\n- REST API endpoints at `/api/v1/sso-settings` are fully registered with access control middleware\n- `SocialService` loads OAuth connectors from the database via `ssosettings.Service.List()`\n- LDAP registers itself as `Reloadable`, enabling hot-reload capability\n- Access control evaluators include both LDAP/SAML and OAuth provider permissions\n- Admin UI exposes provider-specific authentication configuration pages\n- All SSO settings CRUD operations persist to `sso_setting` database table\n\nThis architecture demonstrates a complete compliance control implementation where a single feature flag gates the entire SSO settings infrastructure across feature detection, service initialization, API registration, database persistence, access control evaluation, and UI availability.\n"
